## Additional Professional & Ethical Considerations

This repository is released under the MIT License. However, it is also intended
as a demonstration of architectural thinking, system design discipline, and
responsible engineering practices.

Any use of this software in real-world environments should explicitly consider:

- secure software development practices
- proper handling of sensitive data and credentials
- infrastructure hardening and deployment safety
- alignment with applicable legal and regulatory frameworks

Including, but not limited to:

- GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation)
- DPIA (Data Protection Impact Assessments), where applicable
- secure identity, access, and data handling practices
- infrastructure and domain governance aligned with ICANN-related standards

---

## Engineering Responsibility Statement

This project promotes a set of engineering principles:

- security by design
- verifiability over blind trust
- explicit system behavior
- maintainability over unnecessary complexity
- developer workflow as part of system integrity

This repository is NOT intended to be used in production environments without:

- proper security validation
- contextual architectural adaptation
- compliance and legal review
- operational hardening

